धूमावती:
The name "Dhumavati" means the "smoky one". She is said not to like offerings burnt in a fire that is not smoky. Dhumavati also exists in the form of smoke and roams everywhere at her will. Dhumavati represents ultimate destruction and manifests herself at the time of cosmic dissolution (pralaya) and is "the Void" that exists before creation and after dissolution. 
.
.

मोहिनी :
Mohini is the Hindu goddess of enchantment. She is the only female avatar of the Hindu god Vishnu. She is portrayed as a femme fatale, an enchantress, who maddens lovers and demons, sometimes leading them to their doom.

Transgender model. LGBTQIA+ advocate. Digital trailblazer. Ella D’Verma is so much more than her titles—she’s a force rewriting what representation looks like in India’s fashion and cultural landscape. From becoming the first trans face of a major lingerie brand to being honoured with the Swadesh Samman, Ella is using her voice and visibility to empower a generation. 

Her journey—from growing up as Dev Verma in Delhi to stepping into her truth with fearless grace—is a powerful reminder that identity is not something to hide, but something to celebrate. 🌈
